ef recipe-header__chef--second">By <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><span itemprop="name"><span class="author"><a href="/chef/sarah-cook">Sarah Cook</a></span></span></span></div><div class="recipe-header__magazine"> <a href="//www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&amp;style=Brand&amp;utm_medium=brandsite&amp;utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&amp;utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&amp;utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipeheader' ])"> Magazine subscription – 5 issues for £5 </a></div></div><div class="recipe-header__details-second"><div class="recipe-details"> <section class="recipe-details__item recipe-details__item--cooking-time"><div class="recipe-details__text"><h2 class="element-invisible"></h2> <span class="recipe-details__cooking-time-prep"> <strong>Prep:</strong> <span class="mins">15 mins</span> </span> <span class="recipe-details__cooking-time-cook"> <strong>Cook:</strong> <span class="hrs">8 hrs</span> </span> <span class="recipe-details__cooking-time-full">Plus overnight salting</span></div> </section> <section class="recipe-details__item recipe-details__item--skill-level"><h2 class="element-invisible"></h2> <span class="recipe-details__text"> More effort </span> </section> <section class="recipe-details__item recipe-details__item--servings"><h2 class="element-invisible"></h2> <span class="recipe-details__text" itemprop="recipeYield"> Serves 6 with leftovers </span> </section><meta itemprop="sourceOrganization" content="BBC Good Food" /><meta itemprop="accountablePerson" content="BBC Good Food" /><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2012-11-01" /><meta itemprop="cookTime" content="PT8H" /><meta itemprop="prepTime" content="PT15M" /><meta itemprop="totalTime" content="PT8H15M" /><meta itemprop="recipeCuisine" content="American" /><meta itemprop="recipeCategory" content="Buffet" /><meta itemprop="recipeCategory" content="Main course" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Slow cooked" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Brisket" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Slow-roast" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Tender meat" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Pork sandwich" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Slow-cooked pork" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Bonfire party" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Party" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Halloween party" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Centrepiece" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Glaze" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Glazed" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Sweet glaze" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="More effort" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Bonfire Night" /><meta itemprop="keywords" content="Indulgent" /></div></div><div class="recipe-header__description" itemprop="description"><div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden method__content"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>Coat your pork shoulder with a sweet mustard glaze then slow-roast for soft, tender meat that just falls apart</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="recipe-header__bottom"><div class="recipe-header__share service-links__container"><div class="service-links"><div class="service-label">Share:</div><ul class="service-links-primary"><li class="service-links-facebook first"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A//www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/2604650/maplemustard-pulled-pork&amp;t=Maple-mustard%20pulled%20pork" title="Share on Facebook" class="service-links-facebook service-links-link" rel="nofollow" data-service-name="Facebook"><i class="font-icon font-icon-facebook-large"></i><span class="service-links-text">Facebook</span></a></li><li class="service-links-pinterest"><a href="http://pinterest.com/pin/create/bookmarklet?media=https%3A//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/user-collections/my-colelction-image/2015/1